text: Percy Amos Mozart Stainer (4 October 1888 – 8 July 1967) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League (VFL). == Notes == == External links == * * Category:1888 births Category:1967 deaths Category:Australian rules footballers from Victoria (Australia) Category:North Melbourne Football Club (VFA) players Category:Richmond Football Club players Category:New Norfolk Football Club players Category:St Kilda Football Club players
